



User flow ( this part explains how the user is going to interact with the platform)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 - The USER will open / log into the platform
 - The USER will then select a location
 - When the USER selects a location, we have to show the vehicle rentals STORE's in the location
 - Each STORE will have multiple listing of VEHICLE available in that store
 - When applying the START DATE and END DATE after selecting STORE , USER can see the available VEHICLE's
 - The USER will then select the VEHICLE of choice and BOOK the VEHICLE for those dates
 - When returning the VEHICLE , w.r.t the BOOKING id a INVOICE is generated
 - Each INVOICE will have multiple PAYMENT options for the USER to pay.




List of Classes for the Car Rental system
-----------------------------------------

1. USER - [ id , name , email , phoneNo ]
2. VEHICLE - [ id , type , price/hr, status { available , booked , servicing } ]
3. VEHICLE_INVENTORY_MANAGER - [ INVENTORY ( Map< vehicleId , vehicle > ) ]
4. STORE  - [ id , Name , Address, List<Vehicle>]
5. BOOKING - [ id , userId , vehicleId , fromDate , toDate , type { per day , per hr} , status { confirmed , in progress , completed , closed } ]
6. BOOKING_REPOSITORY - [ Map < id , BOOKING> ]
6. BOOKING_MANAGER - [ vehicle_inventory_manager , Booking_repository ] ( manager the booking, each store has it's own reservation manager )